space.arim.universal.util.concurrent

Class CompetitiveFuture<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.concurrent.CompletableFuture<T>
      • space.arim.universal.util.proxy.ProxiedCompletableFuture<T>
        • space.arim.universal.util.concurrent.CompetitiveFuture<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the object the future will yield
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    CompletionStage<T>, Future<T>

    public class CompetitiveFuture<T>
extends ProxiedCompletableFuture<T>
    A ProxiedCompletableFuture used to change the default Executor used in CompletableFuture's methods executing asynchronous code.
    Used to replace ForkJoinPool.commonPool() as the default executor for method calls.

    In Java 9, there is native support for changing the default executor. See https://www.tutorialspoint.com/java9/java9_completablefuture_api_improvements.htm.
    Author:
    A248

    • Constructor Detail

      • CompetitiveFuture

        protected CompetitiveFuture(CompletableFuture<T> original,
                            Executor executor)
        Creates a CompetitiveFuture with a backing CompletableFuture and Executor.

        The Executor becomes the default Executor used for all CompletionStage methods executiing asynchronous code. In other words, ForkJoinPool.commonPool() is no longer used as the default executor for method calls.
        Parameters:
        original - the original, backing CompletableFuture
        executor - the executor to use for asynchronous execution
